.TH "drm_av_sync_delay" 9 "drm_av_sync_delay" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_av_sync_delay \- compute the HDMI/DP sink audio-video sync delay
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_av_sync_delay
.BI "(struct drm_connector *connector "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_display_mode *mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "connector" 12
connector associated with the HDMI/DP sink
.IP "mode" 12
the display mode
.SH "RETURN"
The HDMI/DP sink's audio-video sync delay in milliseconds or 0 if
the sink doesn't support audio or video.
